My Top 5 this season:

1. Faasle by QB and Jaffer Zaidi (an awesome, touching but underrated melody)
2. Allah u Akbar by Ahmed Jahanzaib and Shafqat Amanat Ali (a beautiful hamd by these vocal maestros, goosebumps!)
3. Sab Maya Hai by Ataullah and Saanwal (nothing can go wrong with an Ataullah song in Coke Studio, and a nice and fresh addition by his son)
4. Baanware by Shuja Haider and Aima Baig (another beautiful ballad which is also a little underrated)
5. Ranjish Hi Sahi by Ali Sethi (amazing performance, breathing new life to this classic)

snippet.textDisplay: I miss the days Rohail Hyatt use to produce Coke studio. This season was very disappointing to say the least. Yes you had some good songs like (Allahu Akbar, Morai naina) but most were just retuned songs of old. Where were Abida Parveen, Sanam Marvi, Tina Sani or the countless other talented singers in Pakistan? Yet Coke studio producers managed to throw Danyal Zafar (a completely unproven artist) to the largest and arguably the most respected platform of Pakistani music. Add to this Aima Baig who is a good singer but simply doesn't fit at the level of Coke Studio and you have a very mediocre season. Pakistan is made up of 4 very diverse provinces, why did the producers not give an equal share to those cultures? I say this as a Punjabi. I am not criticizing here just for no reason, I genuinely believe Pakistani music has no match and Coke studio which brings out the best of that country that has fallen short. :(

snippet.textDisplay:
Am so undecided about this season. The songs were really nice, but none completely stopped me in my tracks.

I often forget to sip on the Coke I often enjoy while watching your show, so riveted do I get. Or, I get excited and immediately share a link with some of my friends in the Far East or the West. These things didn't happen to me even once during this season.

For example, Aaqa gets me all choked up; Paani Da Bulbula makes me grin; Mundari moves me beyond words; Aaya Lariye refuses to allow me to sit still - none of that happened. I watched this season quite passively. (And, seriously, the prevalence of the drum roll throughout this season made me roll my eyes at one point.) There were moments - Aamir Zaki's solo, The beginning of Lal Meri Pat and a few others - where I felt that same joy, but it never sustained.

Visually, too, something was lacking - I couldn't get a sense of space; too many odd angles, 'experimental' framing instances and foreground clutter made me unable to even absorb what I was looking at most of the time.

I listen to your fabulous music as long as I am awake - at work, in my car, before I retire to bed - and am usually in awe of the nuances and the arrangements and the performances. This time, not so much. The songs are growing on me, yes, but I don't find myself returning to them. I have even interrupted a song midway because it made me yearn for a superior performance by the same singer in some other season - and have switched and listened to that one instead.

You guys still set the bar when to comes to the various Global versions of Coke Studio, but this Season, you seem to have lowered it somewhat.

snippet.textDisplay: A season of extremes for me, while most songs were instant classics, some I just couldn't stand beyond 10 seconds(6-7). Favorites- Chha Rahi Kaali Ghata, Naina Moray, Ronay na diya, Laal meri pat, Kaatey na, Ranjish hi sahi, Mujh se pehli si, Baazi, Latthe di chaadar. Top 3 would certainly be Naina Moray, Kaatey na kate and Chha rahi. Winners were the female singers with QB shining through and through. Special mention for Aima Baig, Shuja Haider, Hina Nasrullah and Farhan Saeed. And the ever dependable Javed Bashir and Sajjad Ali provided a solid backbone. Ali Zafar and Ali Noor were disappointing and some forgettably bad re imaginations of Junoon songs remain the lows. Great season overall. The highs far exceed the lows, and few songs will echo through the ages.......reason enough to rejoice.
